27bb4c2e-afa9-4efb-bcae-7bb95ffc8b65.15ea8fa8-0d78-479c-85d1-8c8f4f8b7850.description=
Computes a mathematical operation.

Input Parameters\:
value1 - the first value
value2 - the second value
operator - operation to perform (+,-,*,/,%);

Responses\:
success - the expression was evaluated.
failure - the expression could not be evaluated.

Returns\: the value of the expression.
27bb4c2e-afa9-4efb-bcae-7bb95ffc8b65.1f52417f-a7cc-4633-8e89-5c1583d1b9be.description=Checks if a threshold matches a measuredValue and creates a diagnostic summary if they do not. 
Inputs\:
measuredValue - value measured.
threshold - A threshold to compare the measuredValue against..
Threshold function - (\=\=, \!\=,  >, >\=, <, <\=) the type of threshold
diagnostic name - the name of this diagnostic.
diagnostic so far - The output of previous diagnostics, used for chaining diagnostics together.
recommended resolution - A recommendation for resolving the problem if the measured value is outside the threshold.
     
Responses\:
success - sublist is contained in container.

27bb4c2e-afa9-4efb-bcae-7bb95ffc8b65.description=
Checks for any filesystem errors.
Does not work in Windows 2000, Windows NT 4.0, and Windows Me/98/95.

inputs\:
diagnosticSoFar - used to chain diagnostics together, and get one report. The output of previous diagnostics, or blank.
freespaceThreshold - minimum acceptable % freespace as a decimal.
host - host to check.
user - username to login to host with.
password - password for user.

Responses\:
success - Diagnostic successful.
failure - something went wrong.

Unable to read/process hard drive information
Ensure WMI is running on the remote host, and that a valid username/password were given.
